## 6. Detailed Implementation Guide

### Step 1: GitHub OAuth Setup

**Time Required:** 30 minutes  
**Complexity:** Low

```bash
# 1. Create OAuth App on GitHub
#    Settings → Developer settings → OAuth Apps → New OAuth App
#    - Application name: "CI/CD Portal"
#    - Homepage URL: "https://your-domain.com"
#    - Authorization callback URL: "https://your-domain.com/api/github/oauth/callback"
#    - Save Client ID and Client Secret

# 2. Store in backend .env
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
GITHUB_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-domain.com/api/github/oauth/callback
```

### Step 2: Backend OAuth Implementation

**Time Required:** 2-3 hours  
**Complexity:** Medium

```javascript
// File: backend/src/routes/github.js
// Add OAuth handler endpoint

router.get('/oauth/callback', async (req, res) => {
  const { code, state } = req.query;
  
  try {
    // 1. Exchange code for token
    const token = await exchangeCodeForToken(code);
    
    // 2. Get GitHub user info
    const userInfo = await getGitHubUserInfo(token);
    
    // 3. Find or create user
    let user = await User.findOne({ where: { githubId: userInfo.id } });
    if (!user) {
      user = await User.create({
        githubId: userInfo.id,
        githubUsername: userInfo.login,
        email: userInfo.email,
        githubToken: token
      });
    } else {
      await user.update({ githubToken: token });
    }
    
    // 4. Create JWT
    const jwt = createJWT(user);
    
    // 5. Redirect with token
    res.redirect(`/codespaces?token=${jwt}`);
  } catch (error) {
    res.redirect(`/login?error=${error.message}`);
  }
});
```

### Step 3: Frontend OAuth Implementation

**Time Required:** 2-3 hours  
**Complexity:** Medium

```javascript
// File: frontend/src/components/GitHubOAuthButton.jsx

export function GitHubOAuthButton() {
  const handleConnect = () => {
    const clientId = process.env.REACT_APP_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID;
    const redirectUri = encodeURIComponent(
      `${window.location.origin}/api/github/oauth/callback`
    );
    const state = generateRandomState();
    
    window.location.href = 
      `https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?` +
      `client_id=${clientId}&redirect_uri=${redirectUri}&state=${state}`;
  };
  
  return (
    <button onClick={handleConnect}>
      Connect GitHub Account
    </button>
  );
}
```

